TextEng: Stupid beast. I guess I shall have to kill you too!
No, I'd rather just kill you.
Text: 아니, 그냥 널 죽이는 게 낫겠어.

TextEng: Great. I suppose if we can't communicate you won't be offering me a reward.
Text: 좋아. 의사소통이 안 되면 보상도 없겠네.

TextEng: I have no idea what you just said.
I don't like to share my name.
I am <FullName>. What is your name?
My name is <FirstName>. Who are you?
Yes, it was a close battle.
I have never had such a close brush with death.
Looking for some cute sphinx cousins?
Wait. If you are leaving then I have more questions.
Text: 잠깐. 떠날 거면 질문이 더 있어.

TextEng: That is all the questions I have.
How do I activate the portal?
Could you help me defeat the slaadi that have invaded these ruins?
Text: 이 유적에 침입한 슬라드들을 물리치는 걸 도와줄 수 있어?

TextEng: Do you know anything about these ruins?
How foolish! You should have sealed the door against intruders.
I bet when you saw the basilisks you wished you'd sealed it too.
Text: 바실리스크를 봤을 때 봉인했으면 좋았겠다고 생각했겠지.

TextEng: Is that how the basilisks got in?
We need to discuss my reward.
That's a start. How do I make the stone?
That sounds promising. How does it work?
I guess I will go try that then.
<StartCheck>[Persuade - Intimidate]</Start> You will give me a better reward or you will find that being stone was a much kinder fate.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득 - 위협]</Start> 더 좋은 보상을 주든가. 안 그러면 돌로 변한 게 훨씬 나은 운명이었다는 걸 알게 될 거야.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I think I deserve more than that for saving your life.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 목숨을 구해줬는데 그것보단 더 받아야 할 것 같은데.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade - Intimidate]</Start> You will give me a better reward or you will find that being stone was a much kinder fate.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득 - 위협]</Start> 더 좋은 보상을 주든가. 안 그러면 돌로 변한 게 훨씬 나은 운명이었다는 걸 알게 될 거야.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I think I deserve more than this.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이것보단 더 받아야 할 것 같은데.

TextEng: Fine, let's talk about something else.
Huh? You are still speaking common, right?
Text: 응? 아직 공용어로 말하는 거 맞지?
